model and point out some tests as well as its potential for\ndiscovery of a second Higgs at the LHC. Two additional features of the model\nare: (i) a 5/3 charged quark and (ii) a fermionic top partner with masses in\nthe TeV range.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Dec 2013 21:09:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 31 Jan 2014 18:27:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-03-12"}
